The distance between the midpoint of $\overline{AB}$ and an endpoint of $\overline{AB}$ is equal to half of the length of $\overline{AB}$. By the distance formula,

\begin{align*}
AB &= \sqrt{((t-4)-(-2))^2 + ((-1)-(t+3))^2}\\
&= \sqrt{(t-2)^2+(t+4)^2} \\
&= \sqrt{2t^2 + 4t + 20}
\end{align*}Also, we know that $(AB/2)^2 = t^2/2 \Longrightarrow AB = 2\sqrt{t^2/2} = \sqrt{2t^2}$. Setting these two expressions equal and squaring, we obtain $$AB^2 = 2t^2 = 2t^2 + 4t + 20 \Longrightarrow 4t + 20 = 0.$$Thus, $t = \boxed{-5}$.

First, we use the distributive property to expand the first two factors:

\begin{align*}
4(x-5)(x+8) &= (4\cdot x - 4 \cdot 5) (x+8)\\
&=(4x-20)(x+8)
\end{align*}We use the distributive property again by adding the product of $4x-20$ and $x$ to the product of $4x-20$ and 8:

\begin{align*}
(4x-20)(x+8) &= (4x-20) \cdot x +(4x-20) \cdot 8\\
&= x(4x-20) + 8(4x-20)
\end{align*}
We use the distributive property again and combine like terms:

\begin{align*}
x(4x-20) + 8(4x-20) &= 4x^2 - 20x + 32x - 160\\
&= \boxed{4x^2 + 12x - 160}
\end{align*}

